<unclear/> now than she has been and the Drs think the cnacer compltely destroyed. I'll go and feed my 65 hens and then I'll tell you some more. I wish you could see my flock of chickens. I bought Eleven hens and a rooster last March and now I have 66 pellets and all the old <unclear/> and besides feed since early spring, I will have to <del>call</del> call my flock and will have still more to sell which will buy feed for a good share of the winter. Today I got 9 eggs. I probably wont' roll in riches from chickens but think I can just about make my living with my eggs. Wish you could see my big pile of fire place wood and I have two cards of cookstone wood corded up. and a great big pile of kindling cut. We have never burned a lump of coal since we are in the Ozarks and we have cistern water. We have had a very dry Summer. the gardens were litterally burned up. The summer has been very hot in the daytime but the nights are lovely and cool 

