Mts are beautiful all the time. All the peaches apples and grapes were frozen we are going out into the woods with a neighbor who has a <unclear/> to get wild grapes and later we will go for persimmons butter nuts walnuts hickory nuts and <unclear/>. We are all well now, John was very sick last week but is about well again, He with the children have gone swimming again today, when you come next Summer you must have a bath suit every body goes swimming here. You should see me I can swim quite a little and float perfectly. Even Hilda has her suit and the little thing can just paddle in <del/> water up to her chin. We went for a while evry afternoon. We took Mrs. Brown she had a pick of fear. 
Mona has not been down to swim, went once to watch us since the baby came, we took baby with us. Remember me to your father and mother. And know dear girl that I love you and want you to come next summer. 
Always your <unclear/>
Alice M. Neihardt 